  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6517.5 in BREAKOUT regime and dealers short gamma, they're actively selling into this move above the 6515 amplifying wall (-3859.1M), creating additional downward pressure as the -6.7% 1-min drop confirms the wall_break event. The market is caught between two massive amplifying zones (6515 and 6475), meaning dealers will continue selling pressure until we either reach the 6525 stabilizing wall (+1924.0M) above or crash through to the max negative gamma buyer zone at 6475 (-4717.6M). Watch for violent moves in either direction - any bounce gets sold into by dealers until 6525, while a break below 6515 triggers accelerated selling toward 6475 where dealers become forced buyers.",
